updated docs.
corrected small errors in exporting and importing model. Added some more docs.
Merge branch 'GUROBI_fixes'

Update wedding.py (#323)

* Update wedding.py

Suggestion to use lpSum instead of sum to make code more efficient and aligned with best practice and the other cases. See https://stackoverflow.com/questions/63081381/when-to-use-sum-v-s-lpsum-using-pulp/63081480#63081480 for background. 

The code runs significantly faster.

Note that the import statement varies among the different pulp cases. In this example and the "A Two Stage Production Planning Problem" the statement used is "import pulp". 

Also note that this is my first PR.

* Update wedding_initial.py

Use pulp.lpSum instead of Sum

* Update how_to_export_models.rst

Use pulp.lpSum instead of sum.

commit.message:
model import and export using dictionaries and json. With tests. (#291)

* model import and export using dictionaries and json. With tests.

* the CBC example has issues with mip start. From the logs it appears to be an issue in cbc.

* changes in dict format for problem.

* standardized solvers. big changes to arguments to have the same naming. solver factory via dict and json.

* renamed and reformatted options dictionary and included there additional optional arguments to CBC

* correct but introduced in CPLEX_PY timeLimit. Added test for it.

* more available options for cplex, add check to mipStart. Added available options in tests as example.

* list solvers and default path for CHOCO_CMD

* took out timeLimit from exporting because issues with CHOCO.
